# ============================================================================
# Iceberg parameter coverage
# ============================================================================
# iceberg_scan accepts `version` (snapshot AT-clause), `version_name_format`,
# `metadata_compression_codec`, and friends. Exercising them needs a running
# REST catalog + S3, which lives in inverted_index_view_iceberg.test_slow.
# The snapshot pinning round-trip there covers the only param the resolver
# reads explicitly (pinned_iceberg_snapshot_id).
#
# ============================================================================
# Truly skipped (write-only / encrypted-only / impossible to test here)
# ============================================================================
# CSV write-only: force_quote, prefix, suffix
# CSV operational (no parsing effect): rejects_limit, rejects_scan,
#     rejects_table, store_rejects
# CSV detection-only-with-no-different-effect: auto_type_candidates,
#     files_to_sniff
# CSV aliases of tested params: column_names (= names), column_types/dtypes
#     (= types), date_format (= dateformat), maximum_line_size (= max_line_size),
#     null (= nullstr), timestamp_format (= timestampformat)
# CSV new_line='\r\n': sqllogic substitution preprocessor blocks `\r`.
#     LF byte-offset path is exhaustively covered.
# JSON aliases: date_format (= dateformat), timestampformat (= timestamp_format)
# JSON detection-only: field_appearance_threshold, map_inference_threshold,
#     maximum_sample_files, sample_size
# Parquet operational: debug_use_openssl, parquet_version (write-only),
#     encryption_config (needs encrypted file), schema (struct of complex
#     parquet types -- view body parser doesn't accept this dictionary form)
